       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY2026 President's Budget submittal did not reflect the FY2027 through FY2030 funding. Therefore, an explanation of the changes between the two budget
       positions for FY2027 cannot be made in a relevant manner.

       FY 2027 increased compared to FY 2026 by $49.012 million due to additional investment in sled test construction to prepare for multiple ground tests; increased
       flight test preparation activities to include initial F-15 flight test events; completion of Davis Gun scaled testing; and the development of experimental impact fuze
       technologies to ensure proper system execution and identification of early integration opportunities.

