E. Acquisition Strategy
Development, Test, & Evaluation (DT&E) efforts focus on completing upgrades as well as future architectures and studies to ensure the best use of investment funding.

 SCN acquisition strategy seeks to modernize satellite command and control (C2) network capabilities, Data Transport Receive Network (DTRN), and data transmit,
 receive and transport architectures to increase efficiency and resiliency of satellite operations (SATOPS) and information mobility operations. The approach addresses
 warfighter needs for increased satellite contact capacity, cyber security, automated resource management and operations, and capability resiliency. Early development
 of Enterprise Resource Manager (ERM) leveraged various contracts internal and external to SSC to meet specifications outlined in requirements documents through
 FY2026. In FY 2027, SSC will implement updated acquisition strategies for the next phases of ERM and JAM.

 The Systems Engineering & Integration (SE&I) contractor maintains the DoD Architecture Framework (DoDAF) architecture and requirements baseline for Government
 approval and may perform studies to determine Government options. Limited RDT&E will be applied to Product Support Manager contracts when sustaining engineering
 expertise is needed to finalize Government-approved architectures. Federally Funded Research and Development Center technical depth and breadth will be leveraged
 to ensure SCN modernization efforts are compatible with mission rules and do not pose a risk to safe and cost-effective satellite contacts.




