E. Acquisition Strategy
MW/MT Enhancement effort will be a competitive single task order award in 4th Quarter FY 2024 with options available to be awarded in 3rd Quarter FY 2025 for next
phases of integration and testing.

ITW/AA System of Systems Integration will utilize existing contract vehicles including Integrated Tactical Warning & Attack Assessment (ITW/AA) Systems Engineering
& Integration (SE&I) Contractor Logistics Support (CLS), USAF Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) Operational DevSecOps for ISR NexGen (ODIN),
Massachusetts Institute of Technology Research and Engineering (MITRE), Engineering, Professional and Administrative Support Services (EPASS), General Services
Administration (GSA) Federal Supply Schedules, and Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL). Assessment Management System is in the Software Acquisition Execution
Phase which enables continuous integration and delivery of software capability at the speed of relevance, utilizing Bringing Responsive Operation through Novel
Computing On-Demand II (BRONCO II) contract. The ITW/AA System of Systems program office also intends to utilize the commercial contracting community as well
as partnerships through Space Systems Command (SSC), Space Sensing Directorate, Strategic Missile Warning Acquisition Delta, Data Exploitation/Tools Applications
and Processing Lab (TAP Lab) to lead the Development, Test and Integration of future missile warning capabilities. The use of multiple-award contractual vehicles will
provide a wide range of commercially available products and services that should be able to meet many requirements related to the Integrated Tactical Warning Attack
Assessment (ITW/AA) mission.




