C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
configurations for training-focused sites. Supports research and development activities to generate data/conduct analysis to
support the integration and testing of platform OFP-based simulators.

FY 2026 Plans:
FY 2026 continued additional development, evaluations, and experimentation of system models and OFP-based simulators to
assess OFP interoperability to include but not limited to the addition of E-7, Command and Control capabilities, F-15EX PIAB
Design Study, continued integration of F-22 PIAB, as well as compare OFPs against JSE GSI and SCARS Simulator standards.
FY 2026 also funds evaluation and integration of new technologies including XR/VR Goggle capability, JSE common cockpit
configuration physical device footprint reduction and hardware cost requirements for JSE enabled sites.
FY 2027 Plans:
FY 2027 continues additional development, evaluations, and experimentation of system models and OFP-based simulators to
assess OFP interoperability, to include but not limited to continued integration of E-7 PIAB, Command and Control capabilities,
continued integration of F-22 PIAB, F-15EX PIAB development and associated integration, as well as compare OFPs against JSE
GSI and SCARS Simulator standards. FY 2027 also funds the evaluation and integration of new technologies to include XR/VR
Goggle capability, JSE common cockpit configuration physical device footprint reduction, and hardware cost requirements for JSE
enabled sites.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding increased 7.748 million due to phased development approaches to support Platforms-In-A-Box (PIABs)
development to include E-7 and F-15EX, in addition to other weapons systems and platforms.
Title: JSE Digital Test and Training Ranges (DTTRs)                                                                                       16.833      14.627         22.949
Description: Maintains and expands existing test capabilities, to include platform installation, integration, and verification and
validation activities at the DTTRs and the Joint Integrated Test and Training Centers (JITTCs). Supports ongoing day-to-day digital
test range operations, JSE organic development capability, along with fielded and future Developmental Test & Evaluation (DT&E)
and Operational Test & Evaluation (OT&E) activities. Establishes and expands on hardware in-the-loop testing capability, future
platform testing capability, and continues early experimentation efforts.

FY 2026 Plans:
FY 2026 is a continuation of FY 2025 plans to include, but are not limited to, Joint Technical Baseline (JTB), F-35, F-22, and
Virtual Airborne Threat Solution (VATS) installation, integration, and verification and validation activities. Continued support for
day-to-day digital test and training range operations (vision for JSE is to optimize test reality, capacity, and fidelity by using it
as a closed all-domain digital range, providing a required complement to open-air testing. Additionally, the ability to iteratively
experiment in the JSE environment will drive hyper-refined analyses of alternatives studies and better inform future acquisition

