Title: Modular Drone and Precision Payload                                                                                                 -       24.700         0.000
Description: FY 2027 Mission Partner Environment requirements and resources transition from United States Air Force to DISA.
Funds supported the legacy MPE capabilities including PEGASUS, the Combined Federated Battle Labs Network (CFBLNet),
Command, Control, Communications, Computers, and Interoperability (C4I) Services Operations Group CSOG.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue to develop, integrate, and test an enterprise architectural engineering solution in alignment with the federated mission
networking framework to combine multiple coalition information sharing capabilities, to include modifications or modernizations
necessary to absorb or incorporate legacy capabilities and capacities.
FY 2027 Plans:
FY 2027 Mission Partner Environment requirements and resources transition from United States Air Force to DISA. Funds
supported the legacy MPE capabilities including PEGASUS, the Combined Federated Battle Labs Network (CFBLNet), Command,
Control, Communications, Computers, and Interoperability (C4I) Services Operations Group CSOG.
New resources:
• Support modular drone agnostic accessories and precision payload system. Resources will accelerate the testing, prototyping
and integration of the Zeus Multi-Mission Missile System, an advanced weapon system designed for special operations missions.
This development will close a capability gap caused by 30-40-year-old legacy weapons that are heavy, unguided, expensive,
and incompatible with modern autonomous platforms, enabling scalable precision strike capabilities and improving warfighter
survivability.
• Establish a high rate, low cost composite airframe manufacturing ecosystem using Light-Resin Transfer Molding (LP RTM), rapid
cure resins, and automation.
• Continuing development and production of modular, drone agnostic kinetic and non kinetic accessories (e.g., 40mm
systems, 60/81mm mortar delivery, precision strike variants, electronic warfare (EW) and logistics payloads) that allow mission
reconfiguration in minutes.
• Develop The Multidomain Autonomous Warning System - eXtended (MAWS-X) is an applied research effort to mature a
distributed passive sensing capability for detection and localization of Class 1 and Class 2 unmanned aircraft systems (UAS)
operating in complex operational environments.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Per the MPE Functional Transfer MOA between USAF, DoW CIO and DISA regarding the orderly transition of DoW Mission
Partner Environment (MPE) responsibilities from the USAF to DISA. This memo was signed in Oct 2025. Therefore, there is no
funding programmed for FY27.
