In FY 2026, within PE 1206616SF, Space Advanced Technology Development/Demo, all USSF S&T Vanguard & WARTECH efforts and activities (Transformational
Technology Development effort, Payload Delivery System effort, Rocket Cargo effort, and Navigation Technology Satellite 3 (NTS-3) effort) previously reported and
funded in Project 633834, Integrated Space Technology Demonstrations, were transferred to Project 630321, Space Warfighter Technologist Capabilities, to provide
Congress increased transparency and traceability.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Project is a concentrated effort to improve Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) business practices to accelerate moving emerging technologies into the hands of
the warfighter. Vanguard efforts draw the operational, acquisitions, and technology communities together into coherent teams to solve the hard Science & Technology
(S&T) problems based on Department of the Air Force (DAF) strategic priorities which do not have readily available emerging technology solutions. Teams follow
a disciplined process tailorable to accelerate efforts as deemed necessary by the department. This process (known as WARTECH, for WARfighter / TECHnologist)
leverages discrete progress gates to deliver S&T efforts organized as Vanguard Pathfinders, Vanguard Prospects, and Vanguards. This construct organizes these multi-
disciplinary, capability-focused investments based on characteristics such as effort maturity, established military utility, technical viability and transitionability. Each have
built-in off-ramps to promote transition. The process is overseen by an Executive Committee.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                          FY 2024         FY 2025     FY 2026
Title: Rocket Cargo                                                                                                                              0.000           0.000       8.747
Description: This effort is not a new start. In FY 2026, the Rocket Cargo effort and associated funding transferred within this
Program Element from Project 633834, Integrated Space Technology Demonstrations to Project 630321, Space Warfighter
Technologist Capabilities, to provide increased transparency and traceability of USSF S&T Vanguard and WARTECH efforts and
activities.

The Vanguard, Rocket Cargo, is a Science and Technology (S&T) effort to leverage the multi-billion dollars of commercial
investments in large reusable launch vehicles to extend the commercial rocket capabilities and create a novel DOD solution for
global reach. DAF S&T efforts and resources are focused on the specific areas that are unique to military transport applications.
The S&T objective is to determine the viability, performance, military utility, and business case of the commercial rocket


