C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Embedded GPS/INS - Modernized (EGI-M)                                                                                           75.227      31.700        68.300
Description: Embedded Global Positioning System/Inertial Navigation System - Modernized (EGI-M) is a combined GPS/INS
aircraft position, navigation, and timing system. The program upgrades the legacy EGI design to enhance resiliency against
existing and emerging adversarial navigational warfare threats. Design features, such as interface standardization and software
modularity to incorporate alternative navigation and timing sources, aim to reduce DoW cost and timelines to respond to newly
identified threats and enhance current force capabilities. EGI-M incorporates M-Code and Automatic Dependent Surveillance-
Broadcast (ADS-B) Out compliance capability into EGI receivers while addressing parts obsolescence, reducing configuration
count from 260+ to a desired end-state of 16, and decreasing production and sustainment costs.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete Spiral 1 Formal Qualification Testing. Continue Spiral 2 Software Development. Begin LN-351 PRU system deliveries.
FY 2027 Plans:
Complete LN-351 Delta Hardware Qualification Testing. Complete Spiral 2 Formal Qualification Testing. Continue LN-351 PRU
system deliveries. Begin LN-300 PRU system builds.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding increased due to test/integration of long-term M-code solution for additional platform(s).
Title: Miniaturized Airborne GPS Receiver 2000 - Modernization (MAGR-2K-M)                                                            17.500        8.600         27.700
Description: Miniaturized Airborne GPS Receiver 2000 - Modernization (MAGR-2K-M) is an aircraft GPS receiver. The program
increases MAGR-2K legacy resiliency against existing and emerging adversarial navigational warfare threats while reducing cost
and timelines to incorporate future capabilities in response to emerging threats. MAGR-2K-M incorporates M-Code capability into
MAGR-2K legacy receivers while addressing parts obsolescence and providing a pathway to ADS-B Out implementation. Military
code (M-code) was designed to further improve the anti-jamming capabilities and secure access of the military GPS signals. Since
M-code is transmitted in frequencies already in use by previous military codes, a modernized GPS will deliver improved capability
to counter current and emerging PNT threats and enable military operations in a Navigation Warfare environment where current
legacy receiver performance would be compromised.

FY 2026 Plans:
Program finalizing test and integration of latest GPS Receiver Application Model (GRAM) Software into the MAGR-2K-M receiver
to prepare for fielding. Continue preparing for PEO certification (Milestone C).
FY 2027 Plans:



