Title: Resilient EGI (R-EGI)                                                                                                         107.047      46.000        168.300
Description: Resilient Embedded Global Positioning System/Inertial Navigation System (R-EGI) program establishes a
Government Reference Architecture (GRA) embodying modular open systems architecture (MOSA), enabling and accelerating
the transition and operational insertion of future resilient PNT DoD capabilities. R-EGI delivers improved PNT resiliency through
the rapid design, development, test, and transition of science and technology efforts to operational PNT systems. R-EGI enables
the design and development of various aircraft PNT Line Replaceable Units (LRUs) that are rapidly upgradeable to counter
evolving adversarial threats; the program demonstrates the GRA through prototyping of an open R-EGI LRU. The program
matures, prototypes, and tests PNT technologies/systems and enables transition paths to flow new technologies into the R-EGI
LRU and iterate as required to support the warfighter.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue testing and integration of F-15 Medium Form Factor (MFF) PRUs to prepare for production decision and subsequent
fielding. Continue validation of software development iso a reproducible, government-owned Level 3 Technical Data Package and
execute Functional Configuration Audit/Physical Configuration Audits to enable future competitive procurement.
FY 2027 Plans:
Resume development and testing of the F-16 Large Form Factor (LFF) and testing and integration of the B-52 MFF. Begin
development and testing for AC/MC-130J, C-130J, C-17, KC-135, and SAOC platforms. Continue validation of software
development iso a reproducible, government-owned Level 3 Technical Data Package and execute Functional Configuration Audit/
Physical Configuration Audits to enable future competitive procurement.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding increased due to additional form factor (LFF) development and additional platforms (F-16, B-52, AC/MC-130J, C-130J,
C-17, KC-135, and SAOC).
Title: Positioning Navigation Timing Software Defined User Equipment (PNT SDUE)                                                       15.139      17.721        166.700
Description: Positioning Navigation Timing Software Defined User Equipment (PNT SDUE) will develop a Satellite Navigation
(SATNAV) Software Defined Receiver (SSDR) hosted on a Commercial Off-the-Shelf (COTS) Field Programmable Gate Array
