Remarks
 FFRDC funding increased in FY 2025 and continues through FY 2027 to complete risk reduction efforts that seek to accelerate foundational work for the PNT Software Defined
 User Equipment (PNT SDUE) acquisition program. This effort is defining an agile innovation process so that future capabilities can be more quickly integrated into the open
 architecture/reprogrammable components of the SDUE program of record.

 FINANCIAL PERFORMANCE: MGUE Inc 1 and MGUE Inc 2 efforts are evaluated against traditional Research and Development (R&D) program expenditure benchmarks.
 Unlike many traditional R&D programs, however, the MGUE Inc 1 and MGUE Inc 2 development contracts are Fixed Price Incentive Firm Target (FPIF) contracts with progress
 payments. Ten percent (10%) of incurred costs are withheld until the end of the contract, when they are liquidated. Mandatory funding obligations and progress payment
 withholds will cause the program to lag traditional expenditure benchmarks, painting an inaccurate portrait of overall program execution health.




