B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Protected Tactical SATCOM - Global (PTS-G)                                                                                           82.522     236.822       150.361
Description: PTS-G includes the engineering, development and manufacturing of payload and satellites with X-band and military
Ka-band transponder communication capability and ground infrastructure to include anchor stations that will connect into existing
Protected Anti-jam Tactical SATCOM (PATS) infrastructure developed under the PTES program. Includes ground and software
modifications required beyond the PTES baseline in order to interface with PTS-G segments. Includes ground development,
modifications, and/or services for satellite operations. PTS-G is expected to use existing PTW-capable user modems, but it may
also support transponded communications with other modems. PTW modems for user terminals will be acquired by each Service
and by international partners.

FY 2026 Plans:
The Program Office completed the first delivery order with Astranis, Boeing, Intelsat, Northrop Grumman, and Viasat. The
design and demonstration phase resulted in mature design reviews of proposed PTS-G space vehicles (driving competition
among vendors to deliver SVs with X band and military Ka band payloads) and demonstrations of payload functionality. This
will be followed by the Swarm 1 production award (second delivery order) for four payloads. The program office will continue to
design, demo, engineer, manufacture, and test 4 payloads (2 Ka, 2 X), and procure Joint Hub modems to enable future ground
connectivity. PTS-G will have two efforts; one for X-Band production and another for mil Ka-Band production. FY 2026 activities
include Critical Design Review and SV production start for both the bus and payload, and parts buy in preparation for ground
integration. Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk
reduction, prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities
to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continuing production of PTS-G space vehicles, completing procurement of HW items, and conducting interface checkout of
bus and payload subsystems. The program will begin early integration activities. In addition to space vehicles, the program will
continue with interface checkout of Ground Command and Control system, which includes delivery of Joint hubs, and review
of anchor station facilities to determine necessary changes. Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational
awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain. Activities may include, but are not limited to program office
support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S.
Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and
