D. Acquisition Strategy
PTS-G Acquisition strategy was approved by the SAE on 14 August, 2024. The Program Office awarded an IDIQ to Astranis, Boeing, Intelsat, Northrop Grumman, and
Viasat using the first delivery order for design and development of PTS-G space vehicles (driving competition between vendors with respect to space vehicle type (X-
Band and mil-Ka Band) or within a single space vehicle type). This would be followed by the EMD award, second delivery order, for four payloads to achieve IOC in FY
2029. A subsequent third delivery order for four more space vehicles would achieve FOC in FY 2031. Contract Type is Firm Fixed Price for all PTS-G delivery orders.
The 45th Test Squadron is the PTES Developmental Test Organization and the 4th Test & Evaluation Squadron is the Operational Test organization.




