B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Description: Rapid prototyping of the PTS Space Segment for two PTS-P payloads and bus C2 development/upgrades at the
operating centers for the Ground Segment. Develop, demonstrate, test, and evaluate PTS hardware/software systems and key
system components. Design and develop modular, scalable payloads to support hosted or free-flyer configurations. Includes
integration to host vehicle or purchase of - and integration to - a bus for free-flier configuration. Demonstrate prototype payload
on-orbit performance. Evaluate PTS concept of operations with user participation and enable early use capability opportunities
for warfighters. Mature and validate user requirements. Support development, risk reduction, and integration efforts to launch two
prototype payloads in early FY 2027, one as a hosted payload and one as a free flyer.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete both hosted payload and free flyer PTS prototype payload readiness and space vehicle to launch vehicle integration
in preparation for launch in early FY2027. Continue to mature technology readiness levels of the system's critical technology
elements. Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to demonstrate and test in the
contested space domain.
Other activities include program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, and efforts that
may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging
adversarial threats with speed and agility. Identify and begin implementation of prototype modifications required to enable early
operational use of the prototype payloads.
FY 2027 Plans:
Complete free flyer PTS prototype space vehicle to launch vehicle integration and provide launch support activities. Support
satellite initial checkout for both PTS prototype vehicles and complete all post-launch On-Orbit Demonstration and Test (OODT)
activities and support. Continue supporting existing PTS-P payloads with payload software and ground maturation, continue
integration and testing, develop training materials, and support operational testing to enable early operational use opportunities of
all PTS-P prototypes.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to launch, on-orbit and OODT activities for both PTS hosted payload and free-flyer prototypes.
