Title: PTS-P/R Space Hub End Cryptographic Unit (ECU)                                                                                     12.564      11.302          9.931
Description: Develop National Security Agency (NSA) certified, space-flight qualified, production-ready Space Hub ECUs for
integration with the PTS payloads. Conduct and design development to alleviate critical path risks to the launch of PTS payloads.
Conduct requirements reviews, functional and design reviews, PTS interface development, Interface Control Document (ICD)
coordination, and payload integration with PTS vendors.

FY 2026 Plans:
Initiate the NSA engineering change process for Enhanced PTS-P ECUs and support the NSA delta certification process. Update
ECU parts obsolescence to support the Enhanced PTS-P development and build. Develop ECU engineering development models
for FY27 delivery to payload provider to support early integration and testing.
FY 2027 Plans:
Conclude development of Enhanced PTS-P ECU. Complete key documentation for NSA certification and advance through critical
stages of the process. Conduct quick-action troubleshooting and deficiency resolution for PTS-P ECU contractor during on-
orbit demonstration and test (OODT) activities for PTS prototypes. Finalize ECU engineering development models and deliver
to payload provider to support early integration and testing. Deliver a new software version to resolve discrepancies identified in
SHIELD prototypes. Complete an updated computer board for production representative assemblies and incorporate changes
to address parts obsolescence. Conduct various testing for elements such as TEMPEST, environmental, and electromagnetic
interface.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease due to completion of software development and ECU obsolescence design.
