D. Acquisition Strategy
Program management for the UAI program transitioned from the Fighters & Advanced Aircraft Directorate to the Architecture and Systems Engineering (ASE) group,
Air Force Life Cycle Management Center (AFLCMC), located at Wright Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio. As of August 2025, the ASE group has developed an updated
acquisition strategy and awarded a contract vehicle to curate, mature, integrate, and field several open architecture efforts, including UAI. This contract vehicle leverages
technical expertise via a modular contracting approach that allows for vendor on and offboarding every six months based on performance and phase objectives. This
new acquisition strategy consolidates management of several prior bespoke efforts to drive integration by design across architecture efforts to ease adoption in legacy
and future DAF systems. Lastly, this BPAC funds analysis and support via other Government Agencies, Federally Funded R&D Centers, and advisory/assistance
contractors.




