FY 2026 Plans:
Continue to perform STF testing and certification of COTS products. Address SIB recommendations. Continue the development/
test efforts of aircrew laser eye protection - technical insertion (ALEP-TI), next generation fixed wing helmet, next generation
nuclear flash blindness technology, and improvement of parachute/flotation devices.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continuing development/test efforts on aircrew laser eye protection - technical insertion (ALEP-TI), next generation fixed wing
helmet, next generation nuclear flash blindness technology, improvement of parachute/floatation devices and survival system.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease due to Nuclear flash Blindness Program moving toward production in FY27.
Title: Next Generation Ejection Seat                                                                                                      10.710      11.331         13.652
Description: This effort includes the design, development, and qualification of an upgraded ejection seat escape system
for ACES II-equipped aircraft. The Next Generation Ejection Seat (NGES) safely accommodates greater variation in aircrew
minimum/maximum weights, a minimum aircrew sitting height of 31 inches including the use of Helmet Mounted Displays, and
delivers seat modularity to decreases maintenance costs. It reduces the risk of injuries to the arms and legs (especially due to limb
flail), head, neck, and spinal column as well as decreases parachute landing fall injuries throughout the entire ejection event. This
effort also includes aircraft integration activities.

FY 2026 Plans:
Conclude F-15 seat development and testing and initiate the F-15 Integration phase.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continuing work on the F-15 Integration Contract and Award F-16 Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD) Contract.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Ramp up of F-16 EMD efforts and F-15 integration activities in FY27
